The ANC in Limpopo will hold its eagerly-awaited provincial elective conference this weekend. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge is watching developments. Courtesy of #DStv403 POLOKWANE - ANC Provincial Executive Committee member Dickson Masemola is confident that he will emerge victorious on Sunday. He's up against the incumbent Stanley Mathabatha who wants to continue as ANC Limpopo chairperson. READ: Ekurhuleni ANC elective conference begins after delays Both Mathabatha and Masemola are backing Cyril Ramaphosa as leader of the ANC after the national elective conference in December. "There is no ambiguity about us, and me in particular, that president Cyril Ramaphosa deserves a second term," Masemola said. "We are working very hard and quite understandably, this process that is unfolding beyond this conference, we are looking forward to united Limpopo province behind his leadership."